{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is model judgment quality plus enforcement: whether the real vision model flags explicit content, then policy holds instead of publishes. A stubbed classifier can force \"flagged\" and hide real misses. Workflow rejected because behavior has one agentic decision path (image classification), not multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Run real submissions with a curated explicit-image set through the moderation service using the production vision model endpoint. Assert each item is classified as flagged and persisted in \"held for human review\" state, with no publish event emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly targets robustness of model understanding under obfuscation, which is output-quality dependent and non-deterministic in real models. Deterministic mocks would always pass once configured and cannot expose true classifier weakness. Workflow rejected: single agentic classification decision, not a multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Send an adversarial corpus of hate-speech text variants (leet, homoglyphs, spacing tricks) to the real text moderation model via service API. Assert posts are flagged and routed to review hold, not published.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_lev