s are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is dependency-failure handling and state propagation: unavailable classifier response must route to retry queue and block approval. This is catchable with module wiring plus controlled failure injection; no real model-quality dependency. System rejected because behavior does not require proving OS/network primitives, only correct handling of \"unavailable\" contract.","test_description":"Run orchestrator + queue/repository modules with a vision adapter stub that returns timeout/503/unavailable errors. Submit image posts and assert retry queue enqueue occurs, publish is blocked, and no auto-approval state is written.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.23,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior depends on real model behavior for borderline cases (where stochasticity/sensitivity appears) and whether service consistency controls (e.g., caching/stickiness) actually stabilize outcomes. Mocked deterministic outputs hide this failure mode. Workflow rejected: repeated submissions are repeated single-step judgments, not a chained multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image repeatedly within the defined short window against the real vision moderation path. Assert decision consistency across trials (or within allowed variance policy) and verify resulting hold/publish state is stable per policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.06}}]}
